This paper is related to indoor localization system which is a subfield of computer networks (cs.NI). The proposed model AF-DCGAN is a deep learning model which involves training a neural network to generate new data based on the existing data. This falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The model uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of compressed sensing techniques to reduce the amount of data required for fingerprint construction, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
